.H 2 "substr"
The
.I substr
function is used to perform
substring extracton.
The first argument is the starting position in the string, starting from one.
The second argument is the number of characters to extract.
Thirst and subsequent arguments will be processed to extract sub-strings.
.H 3 "Example"
.TS
center,tab(;);
l l.
Expression;Result
_
[substr 1 1 Peter];P
[substr 3 99 Miller];ller
.TE
.H 3 "See Also"
subst,
patsubst
